-- Poland Gets Bids From GDF, EDF, At Least 2 Others For Enea, Rp.pl Reports
-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 2010-10-06T05:08:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/poland-gets-bids-from-gdf-edf-at-least-2-others-for-enea-rp-pl-reports.html
Poland’s Treasury Ministry received
bids from France’s GDF Suez SA and Electricite de France SA,
Energeticky a Prumyslovy Holding AS of the Czech Republic, and
Kulczyk Holding SA of Poland for a majority stake in third-
largest utility Enea SA, Rp.pl reported, without saying where it
got the information.  Rp.pl said it couldn’t confirm whether Iberdrola SA of
Spain, which according to the website was among five bidders
that the government shortlisted in August for Enea talks, also
placed the final offer yesterday.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
